Sentencas: Improvement of performances of SOFCs/SOECs demands the development of novel materials for its commercially viability and practicability in operations.
Titulo: Development of Pr0.58Sr0.4Fe0.8Co0.2O3-δ-GDC composite cathode for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) application

Sentencas: For air electrode applications novel materials like cobalt based compounds, which offer both ionic and electronic conductivity (MIECs), to achieve high performance are very promising.
Titulo: Development of Pr0.58Sr0.4Fe0.8Co0.2O3-δ-GDC composite cathode for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) application

Sentencas: Among these Pr1-xSrxFe1-yCoyO3-delta (PSCF) seems to be very suitable material for oxygen electrode in SOFCs.
Titulo: Development of Pr0.58Sr0.4Fe0.8Co0.2O3-δ-GDC composite cathode for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) application

Sentencas: In the present study, we have chosen Pr0.58Sr0.4Fe0.8Co0.2O3-delta as the composition of the PSCF material.
Titulo: Development of Pr0.58Sr0.4Fe0.8Co0.2O3-δ-GDC composite cathode for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) application

Sentencas: To overcome the high thermal expansion coefficient of this material with the electrolyte, 10 mol% Gd doped ceria (GDC) is used as the composite material.
Titulo: Development of Pr0.58Sr0.4Fe0.8Co0.2O3-δ-GDC composite cathode for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) application

Sentencas: Chemical compatibility between these two materials was ascertained by the XRD analysis of the calcined composite mixture.
Titulo: Development of Pr0.58Sr0.4Fe0.8Co0.2O3-δ-GDC composite cathode for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) application

Sentencas: Composites of PSCFand GDC with different weight ratio were made and symmetric cells were fabricated using screen printing of the composite ink.
Titulo: Development of Pr0.58Sr0.4Fe0.8Co0.2O3-δ-GDC composite cathode for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) application

Sentencas: Based on the polarisation resistance measurements, PSCF50-GDC50 composite was found to be suitable.
Titulo: Development of Pr0.58Sr0.4Fe0.8Co0.2O3-δ-GDC composite cathode for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) application

Sentencas: From the dilatometric shrinkage curve of the composite pellet, a range of the possible sintering temperatures was identified.

Sentencas: From the microstructural observations and the polarisation resistance measurement of the symmetric cells at 800 degrees C under air, 1100 degrees C was chosen as the most suitable sintering temperature.
Titulo: Development of Pr0.58Sr0.4Fe0.8Co0.2O3-δ-GDC composite cathode for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) application

Sentencas: Optimization of the thickness of the screen printed electrode was carried out.
Titulo: Development of Pr0.58Sr0.4Fe0.8Co0.2O3-δ-GDC composite cathode for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) application

Sentencas: From the symmetric cell measurements, the polarisation resistance of the electrodes having coating thickness from 8 to 9 mu m, has shown the minimum polarisation resistance of 0.12 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C in air atmosphere.
